article.headline: East Tenn. St. 89, Campbell 81
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim Smith led six players in double figures as East Tennessee State held off Campbell 89-81 Thursday night. Smith had 24 points, Travis Strong 18, Brad Nuckles 13 and Ben Rhoda, Dillion Sneed and Courtney Pigram 10 each. East Tennessee (15-8, 12-4 Atlantic Sun) shot 48.8 percent in the first half en route to a 47-37 halftime lead and held off the Camels (8-14, 7-8) by making 19-of-28 free throws to 7-of-12 for Campbell. Smith's 24 points gave him a school record of 2,215 for his career, beating the old record of 2,204 held by Greg Dennis who last played in 1992. The Camels were led by Reggie Bishop with 20 points on 9-of-11 from the floor. Maurice Latham scored 18, Eric Smith 16, Jake Wohlfeil 12 and Ledell Eackles 10. Twenty-nine of Campbell's 65 floor shots were 3-pointers, and 12 were good. ETSU hit 4-of-14 behind the arc.
